# Dependency Injection Rules

This project uses `injectable` + `get_it`. All wiring is code-generated into `lib/src/config/di/injection.config.dart` — never edit that file manually.

---

## Annotation by layer

| Layer | Annotation | Lifecycle |
|-------|-----------|-----------|
| **BLoC** | `@Injectable()` | Factory — new instance every time |
| **UseCase** | `@LazySingleton()` | Created on first use, shared |
| **Repository impl** | `@LazySingleton(as: RepoInterface)` or `@Singleton(as: RepoInterface)` | Prefer lazy; `user_config` uses `@Singleton` alongside its data sources |
| **Data source impl** | `@LazySingleton(as: DataSourceInterface)` or `@Singleton(as: DataSourceInterface)` | Match lifecycle with sibling repository when needed |
| **External / platform deps** | `@module` in `AppModule` | Declared explicitly |

Default to `@LazySingleton` for everything except BLoCs. Only use `@singleton` (eager) in `AppModule` when a dependency must be ready before anything else (e.g. `SharedPreferences` with `@preResolve`).

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — BLoC: factory (new instance per screen)
@Injectable()
class ThemeBloc extends Bloc<ThemeEvent, ThemeState> { ... }

// ✅ GOOD — UseCase
@LazySingleton()
class GetAppThemeModeUseCase extends UseCase<AppThemeMode?, NoParams> { ... }

// ✅ GOOD — Repository impl bound to its interface (@LazySingleton is default; @Singleton when matching other eager deps)
@Singleton(as: UserConfigRepository)
class UserConfigRepositoryImpl implements UserConfigRepository { ... }

// ✅ GOOD — Data source impl bound to its interface
@Singleton(as: UserConfigLocalDataSource)
class UserConfigLocalDataSourceImpl implements UserConfigLocalDataSource { ... }

// ❌ BAD — BLoC as @LazySingleton or @Singleton: all screens share one stale instance
@LazySingleton()
class ThemeBloc extends Bloc<ThemeEvent, ThemeState> { ... }

// ❌ BAD — no interface binding: impl leaks into domain/BLoC
@LazySingleton()
class UserConfigRepositoryImpl implements UserConfigRepository { ... }
```

