## External dependencies → AppModule

Third-party or platform classes that can't be annotated go in `lib/src/config/di/app_module.dart`.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — lib/src/config/di/app_module.dart
@module
abstract class AppModule {
  @singleton
  AppConfig get appConfig => AppConfig.instance;

  @preResolve       // ← use for async init (e.g. SharedPreferences)
  @singleton
  Future<SharedPreferences> get sharedPreferences async =>
      await SharedPreferences.getInstance();

  @lazySingleton
  ApiClient apiClient(TokenStorage tokenStorage, AppConfig config) =>
      ApiClient(ApiConfig(baseUrl: config.baseUrl), tokenStorage);
}

// ❌ BAD — registering external deps inline in main.dart or anywhere else
GetIt.instance.registerSingleton<ApiClient>(ApiClient(...));
```

---

## Constructor injection only

Always receive dependencies through the constructor. Never call `GetIt.instance.get<T>()` or `sl<T>()` inside a class body.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
@LazySingleton()
class GetLocaleUseCase extends UseCase<String?, NoParams> {
  final UserConfigRepository _repo;
  GetLocaleUseCase(this._repo); // injected by injectable
}

// ❌ BAD — service locator pattern inside a class
class GetLocaleUseCase extends UseCase<String?, NoParams> {
  final _repo = GetIt.instance<UserConfigRepository>(); // ❌ hidden dependency
}
```

---

## Always inject by interface, never by implementation

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — depends on the abstract interface
@LazySingleton()
class GetAppThemeModeUseCase {
  final UserConfigRepository _repo; // ← interface
  GetAppThemeModeUseCase(this._repo);
}

// ❌ BAD — depends on the concrete implementation
class GetAppThemeModeUseCase {
  final UserConfigRepositoryImpl _repo; // ← leaks data layer into domain
}
```

