## BLoC provisioning in UI

Since BLoCs are factories, always obtain them via `sl<MyBloc>()` inside `BlocProvider.create:`.
See `bloc-layer.mdc` for the full wrapper/content screen split pattern.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — sl<T>() used inside BlocProvider.create at screen level
BlocProvider(create: (_) => sl<ThemeBloc>()..add(const ThemeStarted()))

// ❌ BAD — sl<T>() called outside BlocProvider (creates unmanaged instance)
final bloc = sl<ThemeBloc>(); // ❌ lifecycle not tied to widget tree
```

See `bloc-screen-structure.mdc` for the full wrapper/content pattern and re-providing rules.
